        <field>Policy_Description__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">ISO 27001 Control A.5.26 requires organizations to establish and maintain an information security incident management process. Security incidents must be detected, reported, assessed, and responded to in a timely manner.</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Legal_Citation__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">ISO/IEC 27001:2022 A.5.26 - Information security incident management</value>
    </values>
    <values>
        <field>Remediation_Steps__c</field>
        <value xsi:type="xsd:string">1. Establish information security incident management process.
2. Define incident classification and severity levels.
3. Implement incident detection and monitoring capabilities.
4. Establish incident response team and procedures.
5. Conduct post-incident reviews and document lessons learned.</value>
    </values>
